01:05:51,649 --> 01:05:54,611
What are we supposed to do?
Jump out of the wedding cake?

701
01:05:54,694 --> 01:05:57,197
Don't be silly.

702
01:06:20,970 --> 01:06:23,056
Welcome to our party. Come in.

703
01:06:27,560 --> 01:06:31,022
Hello. Nice to see you.
Do you know which table you're at?

704
01:06:31,689 --> 01:06:34,192
- No...
- Yes. I do, darling.

705
01:06:34,776 --> 01:06:37,278
I see Phyllis. Come on.

706
01:06:44,119 --> 01:06:46,996
Glad you could make it.
Oren and Barbara Trask.

707
01:06:47,497 --> 01:06:50,208
- Tess McGill. What a great idea.
- Jack Trainer.

708
01:06:50,291 --> 01:06:54,421
- It's so nice to see you again.
- Well, the kids thought it would be fun.

709
01:06:54,504 --> 01:06:58,633
- You must be friends of Mark's.
- Well, let's get you over there.

710
01:06:58,716 --> 01:07:03,471
Actually, I should go powder my bathroom...
nose. Darling, will you wait here?

711
01:07:03,555 --> 01:07:06,307
It's so nice... See you later.

712
01:07:06,558 --> 01:07:09,185
I think I'll get a drink.

713
01:07:09,269 --> 01:07:10,103
Bunny.

714
01:07:21,448 --> 01:07:23,575
Isn't he gorgeous?

715
01:07:35,211 --> 01:07:37,881
Get a grip. Get a grip, Tess. Get a grip.

716
01:07:48,475 --> 01:07:51,394
We're not even invited to this thing, are we?

717
01:07:51,478 --> 01:07:56,232
OK, so we're not exactly invited. But he's here
and we're here. So that makes us...

718
01:07:56,357 --> 01:08:00,069
- Total idiots.
-..in the right place at the right time.

719
01:08:00,153 --> 01:08:02,489
You're like one of those crazed cops.

720
01:08:02,572 --> 01:08:07,368
The kind nobody wants to ride with,
whose partners all end up dead or crazy.

721
01:08:08,077 --> 01:08:10,371
Just act like you belong.

722
01:08:19,005 --> 01:08:21,341
Do you love it or do you hate it?

723
01:08:21,925 --> 01:08:24,552
- Love it.
- So do I.

724
01:08:24,636 --> 01:08:29,390
But Mark says it looks like Nicaragua and
that we're making some kind of statement.

725
01:08:29,474 --> 01:08:32,560
Oh, no. It's just like paradise.

726
01:08:33,144 --> 01:08:36,523
It's like a paradise with little gold palm trees.

727
01:08:38,191 --> 01:08:40,693
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

728
01:08:43,863 --> 01:08:47,617
I hope I'm not being rude, but who are you?

729
01:08:48,993 --> 01:08:52,580
I'm Tess. I'm... I'm a friend of Mark's.

730
01:08:54,124 --> 01:08:58,086
I'm just so happy that
I could be here for you today.

731
01:08:58,920 --> 01:09:02,590
Glorious. Fabulous. Stunning, really.

732
01:09:03,007 --> 01:09:05,635
Super. Elegant. Perfect.

733
01:09:27,031 --> 01:09:29,993
You're right. This is crazy, so let's just go.

734
01:09:32,787 --> 01:09:33,997
Excuse me.

735
01:09:34,122 --> 01:09:37,208
The woman that's dancing with Oren -
what's her name?

736
01:09:37,292 --> 01:09:40,253
- Elizabeth Stubblefield?
- That's right.

737
01:09:41,296 --> 01:09:44,549
- Liz? Beth?
- Bitsy.

738
01:09:44,632 --> 01:09:46,718
Bitsy. That's right.

739
01:09:47,343 --> 01:09:49,095
Jack...

740
01:09:49,179 --> 01:09:51,681
You wanna do it, do it.

741
01:09:53,475 --> 01:09:58,271
Excuse us. Bitsy, don't break my heart
and tell me you don't remember me.

742
01:09:59,063 --> 01:10:02,275
- Of course I do.
- Excuse us.

743
01:10:06,654 --> 01:10:09,115
Talk about a small world, huh?

744
01:10:09,199 --> 01:10:14,704
I mean, here we've just met and yet I feel
I've spent so much time working with you.

745
01:10:14,746 --> 01:10:18,166
In a way. I'm in Mergers and Acquisitions
at Petty Marsh.

746
01:10:19,000 --> 01:10:21,836
I really wish we were having more luck
with your team.

747
01:10:21,961 --> 01:10:24,506
So do I. So do I.

748
01:10:24,589 --> 01:10:27,509
I've been trying to set you up
with a radio network,

749
01:10:27,592 --> 01:10:31,846
but my bosses think you're stuck on
acquiring television and won't even listen.

750
01:10:31,930 --> 01:10:35,016
- Well, that's not true.
- That's what I said.

751
01:10:35,100 --> 01:10:38,228
I said that the man who in 1971
looked into the future

752
01:10:38,311 --> 01:10:41,189
and saw that it was named
microwave technology,

753
01:10:41,314 --> 01:10:46,736
the man who applied Japanese management
principles while others kowtowed to the unions,

754
01:10:46,820 --> 01:10:50,448
the man who saw the Ma Bell break-up
coming from miles away,

755
01:10:50,532 --> 01:10:54,410
this man did not get to be
this man - you, I mean -

756
01:10:54,536 --> 01:10:59,082
by shutting himself off to new ideas.
Am I right or am I right?

757
01:10:59,165 --> 01:11:01,876
- I think you're right.
- Damn straight I'm right.

758
01:11:01,960 --> 01:11:04,170
If you've got the right property, I'd love to hear.

759
01:11:04,254 --> 01:11:06,464
- You would?
- Well, absolutely.

760
01:11:06,548 --> 01:11:08,591
- What looks good now?
- There she is.

761
01:11:08,967 --> 01:11:13,179
I just realised that I...
I'm hogging the father of the bride.

762
01:11:13,263 --> 01:11:17,600
And I see Phyllis coming... What do you say
that I give you a call on Monday?

763
01:11:17,684 --> 01:11:22,355
- Our media consultant is Tim Draper.
- Tim. Right.

764
01:11:22,439 --> 01:11:25,233
- Honey, I'm starved.
- So am I.

765
01:11:25,316 --> 01:11:27,527
- Bye.
- Bye.

766
01:11:29,737 --> 01:11:33,741
Go ahead and laugh. He wants us to meet
with his people first thing Monday.

767
01:11:33,825 --> 01:11:37,620
Oren Trask? The man who said "What if
we sliced the bread before we sold it?"

768
01:11:37,704 --> 01:11:39,164
All right...

769
01:11:39,247 --> 01:11:43,668
No, no, no. I loved it.
I had fun. And you were amazing.

770
01:11:44,419 --> 01:11:46,921
- You think so?
- Amazing.

771
01:11:52,427 --> 01:11:58,808
The Fort Worth station - projected revenues
should read up 8%, not 6%.

772
01:11:59,350 --> 01:12:06,566
And where it says the FCC ruling on
Metro's Memphis transmitter is pending,

773
01:12:06,691 --> 01:12:09,986
that's outdated. FCC approved it Friday.

774
01:12:10,820 --> 01:12:13,323
Doubles the signal reach.

775
01:12:13,865 --> 01:12:16,409
Ups the station's value by 30%.

776
01:12:23,625 --> 01:12:27,337
And now back to our regularly
scheduled programming.

777
01:12:37,138 --> 01:12:39,641
I guess we're ready.

778
01:12:44,813 --> 01:12:47,982
- Trainer and McGill.
- Yes. Top of the stairs.

779
01:13:04,124 --> 01:13:06,543
Are we waiting for Mr Trask?

780
01:13:06,626 --> 01:13:09,462
Mr Trask doesn't sit in at this level.

781
01:13:10,338 --> 01:13:13,299
Of course he doesn't.

782
01:13:13,383 --> 01:13:18,304
Here's the way we see it. Trask Industries
has two important needs to meet at this time.

783
01:13:18,388 --> 01:13:23,601
By acquiring Metro Radio Network,
you nail two birds with one stone...

784
01:13:23,685 --> 01:13:27,856
Excuse me. Do you have any
other proposals besides Metro?

785
01:13:29,065 --> 01:13:32,068
- No. Why?
- Metro's a terrific opportunity.

786
01:13:32,360 --> 01:13:37,866
I'm sure it is, but a Chicago group
just put a bear hug on Metro this morning

787
01:13:37,949 --> 01:13:40,743
and the company's in play.

788
01:13:40,827 --> 01:13:43,413
- Just this morning?
- Who?

789
01:13:43,955 --> 01:13:46,249
The Slade brothers.

790
01:13:46,332 --> 01:13:48,376
Trask isn't aiming at radio anyway.

791
01:13:48,501 --> 01:13:52,380
We certainly don't want
to get into a bidding war.

792
01:13:52,464 --> 01:13:54,841
A moment, please.

793
01:13:54,924 --> 01:13:59,763
Armbrister looks at Metro as if it were part
of his family. He cares who he's selling to.

794
01:13:59,888 --> 01:14:03,016
Yes. And he holds the majority of the stock.

795
01:14:05,393 --> 01:14:10,064
Look. If the Slades are uninvited,
and I'm sure they are,

796
01:14:10,148 --> 01:14:14,944
and Armbrister and Trask can agree
on a deal, then we won't have a war.

797
01:14:15,111 --> 01:14:18,364
If I get Armbrister up here,
will Trask take the meeting?

798
01:14:18,448 --> 01:14:21,409
A lot of ifs. We really
don't want to get involved.

799
01:14:21,618 --> 01:14:25,163
- 24 hours.
- Sorry. Not interested.

800
01:14:33,588 --> 01:14:35,965
Yes, sir.

801
01:14:37,258 --> 01:14:39,552
All right, sir.

802
01:14:44,099 --> 01:14:46,768
Yes, he'll take the meeting.

803
01:14:47,685 --> 01:14:50,688
- That was Mr Trask?
- Yes, it was.

804
01:14:51,898 --> 01:14:54,776
How did he know?

805
01:14:54,901 --> 01:14:56,903
He knows everything.

806
01:16:32,707 --> 01:16:34,793
- Thanks a lot.
- Thanks.

807
01:17:06,324 --> 01:17:08,827
How'd you get this scar?

808
01:17:11,121 --> 01:17:13,498
Some guy pulled a knife in Detroit.

809
01:17:14,666 --> 01:17:16,751
Really?

810
01:17:18,378 --> 01:17:20,463
No. No.

811
01:17:21,297 --> 01:17:24,175
I was 19 and I thought
it'd be cool to have a pierced ear.

812
01:17:24,259 --> 01:17:29,264
My girlfriend stuck the needle through
and I fainted and hit my chin on the toilet.

813
01:17:32,851 --> 01:17:36,855
Have you been telling that story ever since?

814
01:17:36,938 --> 01:17:40,525
You're the only one
who knows the true story.

815
01:17:41,985 --> 01:17:44,487
Except the girlfriend.

816
01:17:46,197 --> 01:17:49,033
I had her disappear.

817
01:17:50,326 --> 01:17:54,873
It's too bad. Nice girl. Real shame.

818
01:18:05,467 --> 01:18:09,304
Jack, there's something that I have to tell you.

819
01:18:19,939 --> 01:18:22,025
Hello.

820
01:18:22,734 --> 01:18:24,819
Hi.

821
01:18:30,366 --> 01:18:32,494
I know. No...

822
01:18:32,619 --> 01:18:35,038
Can't wait.

823
01:18:39,125 --> 01:18:41,795
Yeah, OK. Well, call me when you get in.

824
01:18:43,922 --> 01:18:45,965
OK.

825
01:18:48,051 --> 01:18:50,261
Me too.

826
01:18:50,345 --> 01:18:52,639
OK. Bye.

827
01:18:53,223 --> 01:18:55,308
Bye.

828
01:19:11,616 --> 01:19:14,369
OK... There's this woman.

829
01:19:14,410 --> 01:19:16,830
It's over.

830
01:19:16,913 --> 01:19:21,918
But technically it's not. I just haven't
had a chance to break it off yet.

831
01:19:22,001 --> 01:19:24,754
It's OK. You don't have to explain.

832
01:19:24,838 --> 01:19:29,551
No, really. We were supposed to go away
together a couple of weeks ago

833
01:19:29,676 --> 01:19:31,803
and I was gonna tell her then.

834
01:19:31,886 --> 01:19:34,764
But I had to work through the weekend
and never got there.

835
01:19:34,889 --> 01:19:38,643
It's just a... a timing thing.

836
01:19:39,102 --> 01:19:41,855
It's just she broke her leg skiing
and was laid up

837
01:19:41,980 --> 01:19:46,443
and I couldn't see doing it
over the phone, you know.

838
01:19:46,526 --> 01:19:49,362
Kicking somebody when they're down.

839
01:19:52,449 --> 01:19:56,119
I wouldn't mention it, except
she's in your department at Petty.

840
01:19:56,244 --> 01:20:00,665
- You mentioned her the first time you called.
- Katharine.

841
01:20:02,083 --> 01:20:04,377
Parker. Yeah.

842
01:20:06,838 --> 01:20:09,549
Now what did you wanna tell me?

843
01:20:12,594 --> 01:20:14,679
It's not important.

844
01:20:16,222 --> 01:20:18,308
120, even.

845
01:20:30,945 --> 01:20:33,615
Miss. Miss, you forget your book.

846
01:21:19,911 --> 01:21:22,414
Tess. It's me. I'm back.

847
01:21:22,914 --> 01:21:24,999
Thanks.

848
01:21:28,336 --> 01:21:30,547
She took a muscle relaxant for the flight down.

849
01:21:30,630 --> 01:21:33,383
- Let's all have one, shall we?
- I don't think so.

850
01:21:33,466 --> 01:21:35,510
Telephone. I need a telephone.

851
01:21:35,593 --> 01:21:38,638
Tess, take care of the bags.
I'll meet you at the car.

852
01:21:41,349 --> 01:21:43,435
I love these pills.

853
01:21:43,935 --> 01:21:46,855
Just for a minute, Jack. Please?

854
01:21:47,814 --> 01:21:49,899
I must see you, darling.

855
01:21:50,483 --> 01:21:54,154
My apartment in one hour
and I won't take no for an answer.

856
01:21:54,237 --> 01:21:56,614
No, I won't take no for an answer.

857
01:21:58,908 --> 01:22:01,536
Oh, I'm home. I'm home, I'm home.

858
01:22:03,955 --> 01:22:06,040
Oh, God...

859
01:22:11,588 --> 01:22:14,257
- Did you happen to see this?
- What is it?

860
01:22:14,340 --> 01:22:18,136
It's an outline of your idea
for a Trask radio acquisition.

861
01:22:18,219 --> 01:22:23,600
I was planning to send it over to Jack Trainer.
I thought I'd give your idea one last go-round.

862
01:22:23,683 --> 01:22:28,605
It just occurs to me, looking at it,
that it reads as though it were my idea.

863
01:22:28,688 --> 01:22:33,860
Jack got burned once. He was accused of
stealing a plan for taking a company private.

864
01:22:33,985 --> 01:22:38,323
He's very sticky about the ethics of
reviewing other people's strategies.

865
01:22:38,406 --> 01:22:43,620
He wouldn't do it if it was from a colleague,
and I couldn't say it was a secretary's notion.

866
01:22:43,703 --> 01:22:48,041
Anyway, the point is, Tess,
that I'm still trying to get you heard.

867
01:22:49,417 --> 01:22:54,339
What am I saying? If you had seen it,
you simply would have asked me about it.

868
01:22:55,131 --> 01:22:57,383
Trust.

869
01:22:59,886 --> 01:23:02,472
I'll need help bathing and changing.

870
01:23:05,475 --> 01:23:08,269
I need something to cover this cast.

871
01:23:08,895 --> 01:23:11,189
There's an afghan on the chair.

872
01:23:14,150 --> 01:23:17,028
- Perfect.
- If that'll be all...

873
01:23:17,112 --> 01:23:21,407
And some perfume.
Shalimar, on the dresser.

874
01:23:23,743 --> 01:23:26,246
He loves Shalimar.

875
01:23:27,747 --> 01:23:30,125
- He, who?
- Jack Trainer, who.

876
01:23:30,500 --> 01:23:32,585
He's on his way over.

877
01:23:32,669 --> 01:23:35,380
I have to go. Doctor's appointment.

878
01:23:35,463 --> 01:23:39,217
One last thing? Run down
to the drugstore and get me my pills?

879
01:23:39,300 --> 01:23:42,762
- I really have to go.
- The doctor will understand.

880
01:23:44,431 --> 01:23:46,516
Thanks.

881
01:24:11,541 --> 01:24:14,043
- Who is it?
- Jack.

882
01:24:23,887 --> 01:24:26,389
- Katharine?
- In the bedroom.

883
01:24:31,895 --> 01:24:33,438
Jack.

884
01:24:33,521 --> 01:24:35,607
Katharine.

885
01:24:36,691 --> 01:24:39,152
Boy, did I ever miss you.

886
01:24:40,945 --> 01:24:43,156
- Does it hurt?
- Look at you.

887
01:24:43,281 --> 01:24:47,619
- You said it was urgent, Kath.
- I'd forgotten how damn handsome you are.

888
01:24:48,286 --> 01:24:50,663
Thanks. Look...

889
01:24:50,747 --> 01:24:53,124
I meant what I said. I really am swamped...

890
01:24:53,208 --> 01:24:56,836
Boy, some welcome home.
I haven't even gotten a kiss.

891
01:25:04,385 --> 01:25:08,681
There's some champagne in the little fridge.
You wanna get it for us?

892
01:25:08,765 --> 01:25:12,644
Sure. And then, I really do have to go.

893
01:25:29,536 --> 01:25:32,747
- Where are the glasses?
- Try the dishwasher.

894
01:25:43,341 --> 01:25:45,844
Here you are.

895
01:25:51,015 --> 01:25:53,977
You know I love you, Jack. You know that.

896
01:25:55,979 --> 01:25:57,730
Katharine, I really do have to get going.

897
01:25:57,814 --> 01:26:03,153
These past few weeks, I've heard this
funny little sound, way deep down inside.

898
01:26:03,778 --> 01:26:06,698
Tick, tock. Tick, tock. Tick, tock.

899
01:26:07,490 --> 01:26:11,870
- My biological clock.
- Big deal going. Principals are all meeting...

900
01:26:11,995 --> 01:26:15,707
And I've been thinking "Let's merge."

901
01:26:16,166 --> 01:26:18,168
You and I.

902
01:26:18,251 --> 01:26:22,046
Think of it, darling.
Mr and Mrs Fabulously Happy.

903
01:26:23,965 --> 01:26:27,677
Katharine, it's really not a good time to talk.

904
01:26:28,845 --> 01:26:30,930
You're right.

905
01:26:31,556 --> 01:26:34,100
Can Big Jack come out to play?

906
01:26:34,225 --> 01:26:38,646
- Little Jack really has to get going.
- Little Katie's been so lonely...

907
01:26:38,730 --> 01:26:41,149
No. No. No.

908
01:26:41,232 --> 01:26:43,276
Jack. What is it?

909
01:26:44,736 --> 01:26:48,406
There's something I have to tell you.
There's someone else and I...

910
01:26:48,490 --> 01:26:50,992
There's someone else?

911
01:26:51,826 --> 01:26:55,371
Someone else that I have to be meeting
right now. Big deal going.

912
01:26:55,455 --> 01:26:58,333
Can't be in two places at the same time.

913
01:26:58,416 --> 01:27:00,752
Talk to you later. Bye.

914
01:27:15,433 --> 01:27:17,519
Here we are.

915
01:27:24,109 --> 01:27:26,778
OK, I've gotta run. Sorry. Bye.

916
01:27:35,036 --> 01:27:39,624
Tess, you forgot your notebook.

917
01:27:59,978 --> 01:28:02,730
That little slut.

918
01:28:03,523 --> 01:28:06,568
Goddamn little bitch secretary.

919
01:28:09,863 --> 01:28:11,990
Hi. I have a meeting with Mr Trask.

920
01:28:12,073 --> 01:28:14,159
- Your name, please?
- Tess McGill.

921
01:28:14,242 --> 01:28:16,786
All right. It's at the top of the stairs.

922
01:28:26,796 --> 01:28:28,339
Miss McGill.

923
01:28:28,423 --> 01:28:30,925
Good afternoon. Let me take your coat.

924
01:28:32,719 --> 01:28:35,221
- Thank you.
- This way, please.

925
01:28:37,682 --> 01:28:39,768
Thank you.

926
01:28:49,402 --> 01:28:51,946
- Hi.
- Hi. Is everything OK?

927
01:28:52,030 --> 01:28:56,659
Yeah, yeah. You're the only one
from Petty here so far. What's going on?

928
01:28:56,743 --> 01:28:59,704
- Flying solo on this.
- Good.

929
01:29:00,914 --> 01:29:03,625
Old Armbrister and Trask are over there.

930
01:29:03,708 --> 01:29:07,003
We're waiting to see what colour smoke
comes out of the chimney.

931
01:29:07,128 --> 01:29:11,633
Tell me something. If a colleague of mine
had a strategy they needed help with,

932
01:29:11,716 --> 01:29:15,470
- would you look at it if I asked you to?
- Yeah, sure.

933
01:29:15,720 --> 01:29:20,266
No ethics problem? You know,
open to accusations about stealing?

934
01:29:20,391 --> 01:29:23,895
I look at stuff all the time.
Nobody's ever accused me of stealing.

935
01:29:23,978 --> 01:29:26,606
What's it about?

936
01:29:27,690 --> 01:29:32,278
I don't know. I'm so nervous,
I can't stand still.

937
01:29:34,489 --> 01:29:36,991
You'll be fine.

938
01:29:40,412 --> 01:29:42,914
I love you.

939
01:29:45,208 --> 01:29:47,544
I love you too.

940
01:29:49,421 --> 01:29:52,048
Gentlemen?

941
01:30:10,400 --> 01:30:13,403
There was a story on the news last night

942
01:30:13,486 --> 01:30:16,906
showing life imitating
an old children's riddle.

943
01:30:17,866 --> 01:30:23,538
A truck got stuck at the entrance to the
Holland Tunnel. Too high for the clearance.

944
01:30:23,621 --> 01:30:29,502
For hours, the experts tried to find some way
to unwedge the vehicle, but to no avail.

945
01:30:30,378 --> 01:30:34,007
Finally, a 10-year-old girl in a passing car

946
01:30:34,090 --> 01:30:38,845
suggested simply letting
the air out of the truck's tyres,

947
01:30:38,928 --> 01:30:43,224
thus lowering it to the clearance level,
which they did.

948
01:30:43,308 --> 01:30:45,769
And it worked.

949
01:30:47,061 --> 01:30:52,192
Well, by letting some of the air out of
our strategy to expand into broadcasting,

950
01:30:52,275 --> 01:30:57,655
Miss McGill and Mr Trainer have effectively
shown all of us here at Trask

951
01:30:57,739 --> 01:31:00,450
the light at the end of our tunnel.

952
01:31:05,914 --> 01:31:08,041
Gentlemen and ladies.

953
01:31:08,750 --> 01:31:12,587
I've decided to sell Mr Trask
the Metro Radio System

954
01:31:12,670 --> 01:31:16,466
for $68.5 million in cash and securities.

955
01:31:16,549 --> 01:31:19,761
Now, of course, this is
an agreement in principle.

956
01:31:19,844 --> 01:31:24,516
As to what constitutes principles
in this day and age,

957
01:31:24,641 --> 01:31:28,978
I'm gonna leave that
up to you barracudas to squabble over.

958
01:31:29,062 --> 01:31:31,731
I'm certain they'll want to hear this.

959
01:31:33,358 --> 01:31:36,236
Miss, this is a closed meeting and you can't...

960
01:31:36,319 --> 01:31:37,862
Thank God I'm here.

961
01:31:37,946 --> 01:31:41,282
- What the hell is going on?
- You're being tricked. That's what's going on.

962
01:31:41,366 --> 01:31:45,495
- Katharine, what...
- Jack, just trust me and sit down.

963
01:31:46,371 --> 01:31:51,042
I'm Katharine Parker. I'm an associate partner
in Mergers and Acquisitions at Petty Marsh.

964
01:31:51,126 --> 01:31:53,837
And this woman is my secretary.

965
01:31:55,130 --> 01:31:58,716
- She's not.
- Oh, no? Ask her.

966
01:31:59,008 --> 01:32:03,138
- You're not her secretary.
- I can explain, Jack.

967
01:32:04,597 --> 01:32:07,058
Oh, Jesus. You are her secretary.

968
01:32:07,559 --> 01:32:09,811
While I was laid up with broken bones,

969
01:32:09,894 --> 01:32:14,357
she rifled through my desk, found my memo
outlining a Trask radio acquisition

970
01:32:14,482 --> 01:32:16,860
and has been passing it off as her idea.

971
01:32:16,943 --> 01:32:21,072
It was my idea. She stole it from me, I swear.

972
01:32:21,156 --> 01:32:24,409
Good God, Tess.
Don't you know when to stop?

973
01:32:24,659 --> 01:32:27,162
But you're lying.

974
01:32:36,755 --> 01:32:38,798
Thank you.

975
01:32:39,758 --> 01:32:42,010
Thank you.

976
01:32:47,223 --> 01:32:49,309
Thank you all so much.

977
01:32:50,852 --> 01:32:55,356
The upside is that I have found out
in time to control the damage.

978
01:32:55,440 --> 01:32:59,277
We have containment
and we have a deal on the table.

979
01:32:59,360 --> 01:33:04,449
I say pass me a set of papers
and let's get on with it.

980
01:33:06,034 --> 01:33:08,661
Who's running this thing?

981
01:33:08,745 --> 01:33:11,039
Just a second, please.

982
01:33:13,875 --> 01:33:16,169
I know you don't believe me, but...

983
01:33:17,754 --> 01:33:20,590
It doesn't matter. I'm sorry.

984
01:33:21,591 --> 01:33:23,301
I'm sorry.

985
01:33:23,510 --> 01:33:25,845
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

986
01:33:49,828 --> 01:33:51,913
Well, gentlemen.

987
01:33:52,997 --> 01:33:55,875
The players may have changed,
but the game remains the same.

988
01:33:55,959 --> 01:33:58,878
The name of the game is "Let's make a deal".

989
01:33:59,838 --> 01:34:05,802
If you all turn to page 22 in your prospectus,
I'll take you through the terms of transferral.

990
01:35:35,475 --> 01:35:37,977
Well, they did it.

991
01:35:38,061 --> 01:35:40,605
Yeah. They sure did.

992
01:35:41,856 --> 01:35:44,359
You really look great.

993
01:35:45,401 --> 01:35:48,404
- How are you?
- Good, good.

994
01:35:49,739 --> 01:35:52,659
- Business is great and...
- Mick, did you see me?

995
01:35:52,742 --> 01:35:55,203
I caught it one-handed.

996
01:35:56,454 --> 01:35:59,290
- Hi.
- Hey, Doreen.

997
01:36:01,876 --> 01:36:07,715
And my boat's booked through three weeks
from now. Doreen's workin' the lines for me.

998
01:36:07,799 --> 01:36:10,260
That's great. Really.

999
01:36:12,053 --> 01:36:14,514
So how's life in the fast lane?

1000
01:36:15,223 --> 01:36:17,892
Well, it's fast.

1001
01:36:18,726 --> 01:36:21,020
It's real fast and busy and...

1002
01:36:22,439 --> 01:36:26,192
It's good to see you, Mick.
I guess I'd better get.

1003
01:36:27,068 --> 01:36:29,779
Yeah, it's good to see you too.

1004
01:37:13,198 --> 01:37:18,036
Cyn told us about what happened.
It really bites the big one, Tess. Really.

1005
01:37:18,745 --> 01:37:21,706
- We took up a little collection.
- Thanks.

1006
01:37:21,790 --> 01:37:27,587
It's not much. Just enough to go out and get
toasted some night when you really need it.

1007
01:37:27,670 --> 01:37:30,381
Don't say no. We really wanted to.

1008
01:37:30,465 --> 01:37:33,134
And no paying the Con Ed with it.

1009
01:37:34,344 --> 01:37:36,429
OK. Thanks.

1010
01:37:36,971 --> 01:37:39,682
So what are you gonna do now, huh?

1011
01:37:39,766 --> 01:37:44,020
You know... Play some golf,
redecorate the country house.

1012
01:37:46,106 --> 01:37:50,944
I don't know. Start all over.
Find a job, a place to live.

1013
01:37:52,028 --> 01:37:56,366
And just wise up and not take
the whole thing so seriously.

1014
01:37:56,449 --> 01:37:58,493
I'll be OK.

1015
01:38:03,790 --> 01:38:05,959
- Bye.
- Bye, sweetie.

1016
01:38:06,042 --> 01:38:08,128
- Thank you.
- Miss you.

1017
01:38:09,462 --> 01:38:11,714
- Good luck.
- Bye, Tess.

1018
01:38:12,799 --> 01:38:15,176
- Don't work too hard.
- Bye, Tess.

1019
01:38:27,564 --> 01:38:29,649
Sorry.

1020
01:38:36,364 --> 01:38:40,243
- I've been trying to find you.
- Just leave me alone.

1021
01:38:40,326 --> 01:38:45,331
Just one thing. Was you and me
just part of the scheme too?

1022
01:38:45,790 --> 01:38:47,083
No.

1023
01:38:47,167 --> 01:38:51,379
If I'd told you I was just some secretary,
you never would've taken the meeting.

1024
01:38:51,463 --> 01:38:52,881
Think about it.

1025
01:38:52,964 --> 01:38:57,010
Maybe you'd have fed me a few drinks and
tried to get me into the sack. End of story.

1026
01:38:57,093 --> 01:38:59,637
- That's not true.
- Are you sure about that?

1027
01:38:59,763 --> 01:39:04,768
Can you honestly tell me it wouldn't have
made a difference? Who's fooling who here?

1028
01:39:04,893 --> 01:39:07,729
What's this? More stolen files?

1029
01:39:08,563 --> 01:39:10,774
No, it's my stuff from the desk.

1030
01:39:10,899 --> 01:39:14,944
- Your stuff? Now there's a broad term.
- No, it's my stuff.

1031
01:39:15,069 --> 01:39:18,073
Maybe you can fool these guys
with this saint act,

1032
01:39:18,156 --> 01:39:22,452
but do not ever speak to me again
like we don't know what really happened.

1033
01:39:22,535 --> 01:39:27,457
Tess, this is business.
Let's just bury the hatchet, OK?

1034
01:39:27,832 --> 01:39:32,587
You know where you can bury your hatchet?
Now get your bony ass out of my sight.

1035
01:39:32,670 --> 01:39:38,009
And if you really think that I said I loved you
as part of some scheme, then that is pathetic.

1036
01:39:38,093 --> 01:39:42,097
- My God. She'll stop at nothing.
- What kind of show are you people running?

1037
01:39:42,180 --> 01:39:46,392
Oren, I'm sorry you've had to see this,
but it means nothing to us.

1038
01:39:48,186 --> 01:39:50,480
Jack, let's get upstairs.

1039
01:39:51,481 --> 01:39:53,733
- Not without her.
- Jack.

1040
01:39:53,817 --> 01:39:56,569
Trainer, are you trying to blow this deal?

1041
01:39:57,237 --> 01:40:00,448
No, sir. I'm trying to make sure
that it gets done right.

1042
01:40:00,532 --> 01:40:04,619
Tess put this deal together.
We shouldn't proceed without her.

1043
01:40:04,702 --> 01:40:09,290
And you shouldn't go letting your johnson
make business decisions for you.

1044
01:40:09,374 --> 01:40:12,460
I'm not, sir. I'm telling you, she's your man.

1045
01:40:12,544 --> 01:40:16,297
- What brings you to that conclusion?
- She said so and I believe her.

1046
01:40:16,381 --> 01:40:20,343
I'm afraid that's not good enough.
Now, are you with us or not?

1047
01:40:23,138 --> 01:40:25,557
No.

1048
01:40:25,640 --> 01:40:29,436
Jack, I forgive you. Now get on this elevator.

1049
01:40:31,062 --> 01:40:34,357
- Sorry, Katharine.
- You will be sorry, Jack.

1050
01:40:37,652 --> 01:40:40,613
Ask her to tell you about
the hole in your deal.

1051
01:40:41,823 --> 01:40:44,701
- What hole?
- She's playing games. Let's get going.

1052
01:40:44,784 --> 01:40:47,287
- Fine. Go.
- No. What hole?

1053
01:40:47,495 --> 01:40:49,539
Look.

1054
01:40:50,248 --> 01:40:53,960
The People Page? Now, this is ridiculous.

1055
01:40:54,043 --> 01:40:57,297
"Former Miss America Dawn Bixby
has been house-hunting."

1056
01:40:57,380 --> 01:41:01,092
"Seems Dawn and hot, hot, hot
DJ hubby Slim Slicker

1057
01:41:01,176 --> 01:41:04,262
are getting ready to take
a bite out of the Big Apple."

1058
01:41:04,345 --> 01:41:08,725
- So?
- Slim Slicker's one of Metro's major assets.

1059
01:41:08,808 --> 01:41:13,188
Syndicated to all their stations.
The cornerstone of their programming.

1060
01:41:13,271 --> 01:41:16,483
Lose him and Metro's just
real estate with falling ratings.

1061
01:41:16,566 --> 01:41:18,860
And you're not buying it for a write-off.

1062
01:41:18,943 --> 01:41:21,362
Better make sure he's locked in
before they sign.

1063
01:41:21,446 --> 01:41:24,741
Oren, I have this covered. Upstairs. Shall we?

1064
01:41:24,824 --> 01:41:26,785
- Yes.
- Yes.

1065
01:41:26,868 --> 01:41:30,205
Hear the lady out, sir.
There's another elevator.

1066
01:41:37,712 --> 01:41:39,798
You're on.

1067
01:41:43,593 --> 01:41:44,969
OK.

1068
01:41:45,053 --> 01:41:51,101
This is Forbes. It's the basic article about how
you were looking to get into broadcasting.

1069
01:41:51,184 --> 01:41:56,439
OK, the same day, I'm reading the Post
and there's this item on Bobby Stein,

1070
01:41:56,523 --> 01:42:01,111
the radio guy who does those gross jokes
about Ethiopia and the Betty Ford Center.

1071
01:42:01,194 --> 01:42:05,824
Anyway, he's hosting this charity auction -
real blue bloods, and won't that be funny?

1072
01:42:05,949 --> 01:42:09,994
Now I turn the page to the society stuff
and there's a picture of your daughter.

1073
01:42:10,161 --> 01:42:13,748
Nice picture. And she's helping
to organise the charity ball.

1074
01:42:13,832 --> 01:42:18,128
So I started to think Trask, radio. Trask, radio.

1075
01:42:18,670 --> 01:42:22,549
And then I hooked up with Jack,
and he came on board with Metro,

1076
01:42:22,632 --> 01:42:25,927
and... and so now here we are.

1077
01:42:39,065 --> 01:42:42,402
Oren, we really don't have
any more time for fairy tales.

1078
01:42:42,485 --> 01:42:45,780
Miss Parker, let me ask you a question.

1079
01:42:45,864 --> 01:42:49,784
How did you come up the idea
for Trask to buy up Metro?

1080
01:42:49,909 --> 01:42:52,203
How did I...?

1081
01:42:52,871 --> 01:42:55,832
Well, let's see. The...

1082
01:42:57,083 --> 01:43:00,587
The impulse. What led you
to put the two together?

1083
01:43:02,630 --> 01:43:07,135
Well, I would have to check my files.
I can't recall exactly the...

1084
01:43:07,260 --> 01:43:10,722
Generally. It's not as if
it was in the mainstream.

1085
01:43:12,390 --> 01:43:15,101
You know, it would have to be the...

1086
01:43:17,979 --> 01:43:20,732
Jack, help me out here.

1087
01:43:25,153 --> 01:43:28,907
Oren, I beg your pardon,
but if you are insinuating...

1088
01:43:28,990 --> 01:43:34,579
Miss Parker, if I were you, I'd go to your office
and take a long last look around.

1089
01:43:35,163 --> 01:43:40,668
Because in about five minutes, I'm going
to see to it that you get the boot but good.

1090
01:43:41,377 --> 01:43:45,006
Oren, this is a simple misunderstanding.
I... You cannot...

1091
01:43:45,090 --> 01:43:47,300
I can and I will.

1092
01:43:47,383 --> 01:43:50,178
Now get your... What did you call it?

1093
01:43:50,845 --> 01:43:53,556
- Bony ass.
- Right.

1094
01:43:53,640 --> 01:43:56,434
..bony ass out of my sight.

1095
01:43:56,768 --> 01:44:02,357
I'm sorry, but I simply
won't stand for that kind of talk.

1096
01:44:04,651 --> 01:44:06,945
Will you excuse me, please?

1097
01:44:17,872 --> 01:44:20,834
Why didn't you tell us all this
in the boardroom that day?

1098
01:44:20,917 --> 01:44:23,628
No one was gonna listen, sir. Not to me.

1099
01:44:23,962 --> 01:44:27,715
You can bend the rules upstairs,
but not while you're trying to get there.

1100
01:44:27,799 --> 01:44:31,469
And someone like me
can't get there without bending the rules.

1101
01:44:31,553 --> 01:44:37,350
You've got a real fire in your belly. Or was
this just a one-time stunt that you pulled?

1102
01:44:37,434 --> 01:44:41,604
I have something in my belly,
but I think it's nervous knots.

1103
01:44:42,313 --> 01:44:45,567
Are you willing to go out on that limb
every day, working for me?

1104
01:44:45,650 --> 01:44:48,194
- Legitimately?
- Yes, sir.

1105
01:44:48,278 --> 01:44:51,865
- Have to be at the entry level. Any problem?
- No, sir.

1106
01:44:52,657 --> 01:44:55,869
- Gumption, Miss McGill.
- Yes, sir.

1107
01:44:55,952 --> 01:44:58,037
- See you tomorrow.
- OK.

1108
01:44:58,580 --> 01:45:03,126
Trainer, Dwayne. Let's go to my office
and see about Slim whatshisname's contract.

1109
01:45:03,251 --> 01:45:05,712
Be right with you, sir.

1110
01:45:11,342 --> 01:45:14,471
- Way to go, Tess. Way to go.
- Beauty.

1111
01:45:41,081 --> 01:45:43,792
For you. You like it?

1112
01:45:47,420 --> 01:45:51,257
Peanut butter and jelly sandwich.
Milk money.

1113
01:45:53,093 --> 01:45:55,428
Twinkies.

1114
01:45:55,512 --> 01:45:58,306
Pen, pencil, ruler. Apple for the teacher.

1115
01:45:59,057 --> 01:46:05,271
Remember. Play nice with the other kids
and make sure you're home before dark.

1116
01:46:18,993 --> 01:46:20,245
Hi. Tess McGill.

1117
01:46:20,328 --> 01:46:22,372
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1118
01:46:22,455 --> 01:46:27,460
The director is out sick today, so she'll
want to see you first thing tomorrow.

1119
01:46:27,544 --> 01:46:31,756
Miss Baxter's already up there.
She'll show you the layout.

1120
01:46:32,298 --> 01:46:36,094
- It's all the way at the end of the hall.
- All right. Thank you.

1121
01:46:36,177 --> 01:46:38,263
You're welcome.

1122
01:46:47,564 --> 01:46:50,316
Anybody'll be an improvement
over that terrorist.

1123
01:46:50,400 --> 01:46:53,319
I mean, something semi-human.

1124
01:47:05,206 --> 01:47:07,792
I didn't hear you come in.

1125
01:47:07,876 --> 01:47:10,253
- I'm Alice Baxter.
- Tess McGill.

1126
01:47:11,087 --> 01:47:13,798
I was just using the phone.

1127
01:47:14,632 --> 01:47:17,093
Yes, well, that happens.

1128
01:47:18,178 --> 01:47:21,306
- How about some coffee?
- Sure. Just tell me where.

1129
01:47:21,389 --> 01:47:24,434
No, I'll get it. How?

1130
01:47:24,893 --> 01:47:27,145
Milk and sugar, please.

1131
01:47:27,228 --> 01:47:29,314
Thank you.

1132
01:47:50,585 --> 01:47:52,670
- Miss McGill.
- Yes?

1133
01:47:53,463 --> 01:47:56,299
That's your desk, in there.

1134
01:47:57,133 --> 01:47:59,344
I don't think so.

1135
01:47:59,469 --> 01:48:01,971
Oh, yes. I sit out here.

1136
01:48:03,223 --> 01:48:06,559
I'm sorry. I thought
the secretary would sit out here.

1137
01:48:06,643 --> 01:48:09,354
That's right. I'm the secretary.

1138
01:48:11,106 --> 01:48:13,691
If it's OK, I prefer "assistant".

1139
01:48:29,124 --> 01:48:32,794
You've got a 10 o'clock meeting
with Slater from Development - here.

1140
01:48:32,877 --> 01:48:37,048
11 o'clock with Donohue
from Logistics - his office on 23.

1141
01:48:37,173 --> 01:48:40,927
And lunch with Mr Trask -
his office downtown, one o'clock.

1142
01:48:42,011 --> 01:48:46,766
It's all right there on the computer.
Just hit shift-S for your schedule.

1143
01:48:54,649 --> 01:48:59,738
When I saw you in here
on the phone with your feet up,

1144
01:49:00,321 --> 01:49:02,824
I figured this was your office.

1145
01:49:04,409 --> 01:49:08,538
I'm sorry about that, Miss McGill.
It won't happen again ever.

1146
01:49:08,663 --> 01:49:10,415
It's OK.

1147
01:49:11,583 --> 01:49:15,712
Maybe now would be a good time
to go over what you expect of me.

1148
01:49:20,800 --> 01:49:23,803
I... I expect you to call me Tess.

1149
01:49:24,763 --> 01:49:28,892
I don't expect you to fetch me coffee
unless you're getting some for yourself.

1150
01:49:29,017 --> 01:49:35,148
And the rest we'll just make up
as we go along.

1151
01:49:36,232 --> 01:49:38,318
OK?

1152
01:49:40,612 --> 01:49:42,697
OK.

1153
01:49:44,199 --> 01:49:48,286
- I'll be right outside if you need anything.
- Fine.

1154
01:50:00,715 --> 01:50:02,509
Cyn.

1155
01:50:02,634 --> 01:50:04,928
Guess where I am?
